Jenni EvansCape Town - Thirty firefighters worked through Friday night and Saturday morning to put out a fire on Table Mountain.The fire started near the Maclear Beacon on the eastern side of the world heritage site famous for its fauna and flora and sweeping sea views.''It was brought under control by 06:50,'' said JP Smith, the city's mayoral committee member for safety and security.Non-profit Volunteer Wildlife Service posted a picture of exhausted fire fighters at the top of the mountain after their trying night.A long night on #TableMountainFire shows in the faces of exhausted crew. But where else in the world do you take a cable car to fight fire. pic.twitter.com/bNnBqndQQj24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.